### [**V. P. Patel and Brothers v. Laxmi Complex Commercial Premises Coop. Society Ltd. 2025 INSC 1437 \- Art. 227 Constitution**](https://www.caseciter.com/content/files/2025/12/V.-P.-Patel-and-Brothers-v.-Laxmi-Complex-Commercial-Premises-Coop.-Society-Ltd.-2025-INSC-1437---Art.-227-Constitution-.pdf)

**Constitution of India \- Article 227 \-** High Court refused to interfere with the order of ‘unilateral deemed conveyance’ issued by the Competent Authority under the Maharashtra Ownership Flats (Regulation of the Promotion of Construction, Sale, Management and Transfer) Act \- Dismissing SLP, SC observed: once the procedure is found proper there cannot be a judicial review on the merits, which also has not been effectively pleaded. (Para 7\)

