### [**Bal Kumar Patel @ Raj Kumar vs State of U.P.; 2025 INSC 1378 \-CrPC/BNSS \- Withdrawal From Prosecution \-Cases Against MPs & MLAs**](https://www.caseciter.com/content/files/2025/12/Bal-Kumar-Patel-@-Raj-Kumar-vs-State-of-U.P.--2025-INSC-1378--CrPC-BNSS---Withdrawal-From-Prosecution--Cases-Against-MPs---MLAs.pdf)

**Code of Criminal Procedure 1973 \- Section 321** \- Applications before High Court for permission of withdrawal of prosecution in cases concerning MPs or MLAs \- Public Prosecutor who has a duty to assist the Court ‘with a fairly considered view’ on the case, in his application and in the interest of justice should disclose all reasons that weighed with them to put forward this application to the Court \- This application disclosing the reasons for withdrawal of prosecution given by the Public Prosecutor as also the records of the case should be before the High Court which would exercise its judicial mind and give a reasoned order, granting or denying such permission. (Para 9\)  
