### [**Saurav Narayan v. Union of India \- Reservation In Orgs Receiving Grant-in-Aid**](https://www.caseciter.com/content/files/2025/11/Saurav-Narayan-v.-Union-of-India---Reservation-In-Orgs-Receiving-Grant-in-Aid.pdf)

**Reservation** \- Writ petition seeking reservation in services of institutions /autonomous bodies/organisations, which are receiving grant-in-aid from the Government \- Disposed with liberty to the petitioners to submit a comprehensive representation \- SC observed: Prescription of reservation in any particular organisation, conditionally or unconditionally, is the ultimate prerogative of the policy-maker/Legislature- It may not be prudent for this Court to express any definite opinion in relation thereto. (Para 7\)

