### [**Varun Kumar Alias Sonu v. State of Himachal Pradesh 2025 INSC 1232 \- Rape \- Minor's Consent Immaterial**](https://www.caseciter.com/content/files/2025/10/Varun-Kumar-Alias-Sonu-v.-State-of-Himachal-Pradesh-2025-INSC-1232---Rape---Minor-s-Consent-Immaterial.pdf)

**Indian Penal Code 1860 \- Section 376 \-** SC upholds a rape conviction and observed: Medical evidence does not rule out the possibility of rape upon the victim. Even assuming that the victim had wilfully volunteered to sexual intercourse, this aspect becomes immaterial, as the victim was a minor on the date of the incident in question. (Para 15\)

