### [**Saldanha Real Estate Private Limited vs Bishop John Rodrigues**](https://www.caseciter.com/content/files/2025/08/Saldanha-Real-Estate-Private-Limited-vs-Bishop-John-Rodrigues-2025-INSC-1016--Maharashtra-Slum-Areas-Act.pdf) **[2025 INSC 1016 \-Maharashtra Slum Areas Act](https://www.caseciter.com/saldanha-real-estate-private-limited-vs-bishop-john-rodrigues-2025-insc-1016-maharashtra-slum-areas-act/)**

**Maharashtra Slum Areas (Improvement, Clearance and Redevelopment) Act \-** The holistic interpretation of the Slums Act made by this Court in [*Tarabai*](https://www.caseciter.com/tarabai-nagar-co-op-hog-society-proposed-vs-state-of-maharashtra-2025-insc-1015-maharashtra-slum-areas-improvement-clearance-and-redevelopment-act/) case is also squarely applicable on post-2018 Amendment actions/events, barring the now legislatively stipulated timeline within which a redevelopment scheme has to be submitted by an interested landowner. (Para 25\)

**Constitution of India \- Article 226 \-** High Court, in exercise of its plenary jurisdiction under Article 226 of the Constitution, can prevent or annul any executive overreach, arbitrary decision-making process, action tainted with mala fides, or colourable exercise of power. (Para 18\)

