### [**Suresh vs State of Uttar Pradesh 2025 INSC 918 \- S. 35 Evidence Act \- Non Govt. School**](https://www.caseciter.com/suresh-vs-state-of-uttar-pradesh-2025-insc-918-s-35-evidence-act-non-govt-school/#gsc.tab=0)

**Indian Evidence Act 1872 \- Section 35** \- When the school – is not a Government School and thus, the records maintained by the said School would not be ‘public documents’. Moreover, the Headmaster/Principal of such a School cannot be said to be a ‘public servant’ for the purposes of the Evidence Act. (Para 19\)

**Juvenile Justice (Care and Protection of Children) Act, 2000 \-** SC set aside the Trial Court holding the Respondent to be a ‘juvenile’.

