### [**Reliance General Insurance Company Limited vs Swati Sharma 2025 INSC 487 \- Motor Accident Compensation \- Insurer**](https://www.caseciter.com/reliance-general-insurance-company-limited-vs-swati-sharma-2025-insc-487-motor-accident-compensation-insurer/)

**Motor Accident Compensation** \- The insurer, who has insured the vehicle is bound to indemnify the owner of the vehicle who has the vicarious liability as against the negligence of his employee. (Para 6\)

### ---

[**R. Baiju vs State of Kerala 2025 INSC 488 \- S.120B IPC \- Conspiracy**](https://www.caseciter.com/r-baiju-vs-state-of-kerala-2025-insc-488-s-120b-ipc-conspiracy/)

**Indian Penal Code 1860 \- Section 120B,149-** By the very nature of the offence of conspiracy, being hatched in secrecy, no evidence of the common intention of the conspirators can be normally produced before Court. The offence can be proved largely by inferences from the acts committed or words spoken by the conspirators in pursuance of a common intention. (Para 18\)

